# Sociocultral Theory

Not one theory but a group of ttheories

Learning is an activity that is embedded withing social, cultural, and historical context

Emphasize learning in real world contexts

>Situated learning
	Learning occurs as an indivual moves from being on the edges of a community ot more full participation in a community of practice (a community that does a specific type of work or hobby)
	Learners begin to identify with this community

Current research involves fostering opportutnies for learners to work and fixing "identity gaps" that exist for minority groups in CEd.

